# LAMMPS Input File
# Licensed under CC BY 4.0
# A Set of Materials-Science Tutorials for the LAMMPS Simulation Package
# Tutorial 14: chemical short-range order in a high-entropy alloy
#
# Same hybrid MD/MC protocol as sro-hot.lmp (1300 K), but with the eight-element
# MEAM potential of Sharifi and Wick, Comput. Mater. Sci. 248, 113595 (2025),
# fitted to the mechanical properties of complex concentrated alloys.  Its
# overly negative mixing enthalpies (see mixing-sharifi.lmp) drive a spurious
# partitioning into (Co,Fe)-rich and (Ni,Cr)-rich regions.
#
# The potential files library.meam and FeMnNiTiCuCrCoAl.meam are included,
# obtained from the NIST Interatomic Potentials Repository entry:
# https://www.ctcms.nist.gov/potentials/entry/2025--Sharifi-H-Wick-C-D--Fe-Mn-Ni-Ti-Cu-Cr-Co-Al/
#
# CAUTION: the indices in the parameter file FeMnNiTiCuCrCoAl.meam refer to the
# element order of its file name (Fe Mn Ni Ti Cu Cr Co Al).  That exact list
# must be given in the pair_coeff command below; only the per-type mapping at
# the end may be changed.  A different list silently reassigns all pair
# parameters to the wrong element pairs.

units metal
atom_style atomic
boundary p p p

variable T equal 1300.0

# 1) build a random equimolar CoCrFeNi crystal (fcc, 5x5x5 = 500 atoms)
lattice fcc 3.56
region box block 0 5 0 5 0 5
create_box 4 box
create_atoms 1 box
# randomly assign exactly one quarter of the sites to each element
set group all type/subset 2 125 12345
set type 1   type/subset 3 125 23456
set type 1   type/subset 4 125 34567
mass 1 58.933   # Co
mass 2 51.996   # Cr
mass 3 55.845   # Fe
mass 4 58.693   # Ni
pair_style meam
pair_coeff * * library.meam Fe Mn Ni Ti Cu Cr Co Al FeMnNiTiCuCrCoAl.meam Co Cr Fe Ni

variable peat equal pe/count(all)

# 2) thermalize the atomic positions at temperature T (no swaps yet)
velocity all create ${T} 9988 mom yes rot yes dist gaussian
fix md all npt temp ${T} ${T} 0.1 iso 0.0 0.0 1.0
thermo 500
thermo_style custom step temp pe press
run 2000
write_dump all custom random-sharifi.dump id type x y z modify sort id

# 3) hybrid MD/MC: every 40 MD steps attempt 40 identity swaps for each
#    element pair, accepted with the Metropolis criterion at temperature T
fix s12 all atom/swap 40 40 701 ${T} types 1 2
fix s13 all atom/swap 40 40 702 ${T} types 1 3
fix s14 all atom/swap 40 40 703 ${T} types 1 4
fix s23 all atom/swap 40 40 704 ${T} types 2 3
fix s24 all atom/swap 40 40 705 ${T} types 2 4
fix s34 all atom/swap 40 40 706 ${T} types 3 4
fix peout all ave/time 100 1 100 v_peat file energy-sharifi.dat
dump traj all custom 500 anneal-sharifi.dump id type x y z
dump_modify traj sort id
run 12000
write_dump all custom ordered-sharifi.dump id type x y z modify sort id
write_data ordered-sharifi.data
